Wash and dry produce.

Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}; halve lettuce lengthwise (don't separate into leaves!). Finely slice half the lettuce crosswise; cut remaining lettuce into two wedges (four wedges for 4 servings). Thinly slice @tomato{1} into rounds.

Halve and toast @demi-baguette{2}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} and @Italian dressing{1.5%ounce}.

Fill toasted baguettes with @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}(shredded), @smoked deli ham{8%ounce}, sliced lettuce, tomato rounds, and half the creamy dressing.

Halve subs on a diagonal.

Divide subs and lettuce wedges between plates. Drizzle wedges with remaining creamy dressing and serve.

> Whether you call them subs, hoagies, heroes, or grinders, these substantial
> sandwiches deliver on flavor! A crisp wedge salad served alongside completes
> this quick and tasty dish.